Information
------------------------------

Saving the Cyber Sex Girls: Stacey Dooley Investigates
The journalist presents the first of two films examining the worst places in the world to be female, investigating why some young women today live in such dangerous, desperate and degrading conditions. In this edition, Stacey travels to the Philippines to examine the growing cyber-sex industry, in which girls who are rarely let out and often underage must perform on webcams and be photographed for a global online audience. She learns how poverty combined with cheap internet access has led to an increasing number of girls being exposed to online sexual abuse and goes undercover with the police on a major sting operation.
